text.section:
In accordance with the provisions of subsection (f) of this section, the Director of the Maryland Energy Administration or the designee of the Director shall:
administer the Fund;
develop plans, prepare and submit proposals to the Governor for Fund use, and undertake any action that is necessary to obtain for the Fund all energy overcharge refunds and judgment awards to which the citizens of the State have a legal entitlement;
assess and determine the respective needs of the citizens of the State and develop recommendations for the allocation and disbursement of funds in accordance with those needs pursuant to the provisions of subsection (f) of this section;
conduct public hearings at least twice a year at times and places the Director or the designee of the Director determines; and
perform other duties as may be assigned by the Governor.

section.section:
The Fund shall be expended:
for emergency energy assistance provided under § 5-5A-07(a) of the Human Services Article;
for energy assistance programs provided under § 5-5A-07(b) of the Human Services Article;
for energy assistance and weatherization programs provided under § 4-211(c) of the Housing and Community Development Article and Title 9, Subtitle 20 of the State Government Article;
for energy extension service and low-income home-energy programs provided under 42 U.S.C. §§ 7001 through 7011 and 8621 through 8629;
for other energy assistance or weatherization programs meeting the federal restitutive objectives governing the distribution of overcharge refunds to the states;
for any other program within the definition of "energy conservation programs" as provided by Pub. L. No. 97-377, 96 Stat. 1830, § 155 (1982) and subsequent amendments, including the State Energy Efficiency Programs Improvement Act of 1990, Pub. Law No. 101-440;
for energy efficiency and economic development loans provided under Title 9, Subtitle 20A of the State Government Article; or
for any other purpose required as a condition of their acceptance.
